An armed suspect was shot in a shootout during an alleged attempted cash-in-transit heist at the Hillcrest Corner shopping centre on Friday, reports the Highway Mail. According to a source, armed men attempted to rob an SBV carrier near the banking hall at the shopping centre. Shots were fired during the cash-in-transit heist, and one of the armed robbers was hit and escaped empty-handed on foot. The SAPS are in pursuit. There have been no other reported injuries. Centre management was unable to comment, as they did not have all of the facts and figures but said a comment would be posted on the mall s Facebook page later today regarding the incident. Screenshot of the Hillcrest Corner Facebook page. Picture: Facebook Caxton News Service For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.